  "exec_summary": "The European Securities and Markets Authority's MiCA regulation has taken full effect, resulting in a significant impact on the EU's crypto industry, with many firms facing shutdown due to inability to meet the new requirements. As of the July 1 deadline, 244 MiCA licenses have been issued by EU countries, with Germany accounting for nearly a quarter of all approvals. The European Banking Authority has also announced efforts to simplify supervision for a stronger EU banking framework, aiming to streamline regulatory processes. Meanwhile, the National Bank of Belgium and the Financial Services and Markets Authority are expected to closely monitor the implementation of MiCA and its effects on the Belgian financial sector.",
